                            </div>
                            <p>Generally, controllers are full of methods, but with minimal code like above. Controllers manage access,&nbsp;leverage models and render views. The bulk of intelligence should be built into your models and the views should generally produce relatively simple template operations.</p>
                            <p>By default, Yii will render <code class="inline">/views/layouts/main.php</code> around your index view in <code class="inline">/views/site/index.php</code>. The <code class="inline">main.php</code> layout provides the HTML and CSS structure to the page, e.g. the toolbar and content area.&nbsp;Inside <code class="inline">main.php</code>, you'll see a brief call out to the content:</p>
